1
00:00:09,667 --> 00:00:13,458
- [light guitar music plays]
- [radio tuning in]

2
00:00:14,917 --> 00:00:16,667
[announcer] <i>It has now been seven months</i>

3
00:00:16,750 --> 00:00:19,042
<i>since Spain
began applying European measures</i>

4
00:00:19,125 --> 00:00:21,708
<i>to tackle the shortage of basic resources.</i>

5
00:00:21,792 --> 00:00:24,417
<i>The plan, called "Not Enough for All,"</i>

6
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:26,083
<i>has started to produce results.</i>

7
00:00:26,167 --> 00:00:29,125
<i>But for now, Spain,
as well as its neighboring countries,</i>

8
00:00:29,208 --> 00:00:31,917
<i>won't be able
to sustain dependent citizens until...</i>

9
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,000
[radio shuts off]

10
00:00:34,333 --> 00:00:37,375
Get to your positions.
Come on. Same as last time.

11
00:00:37,458 --> 00:00:38,875
- Let's do this.
- [man 1] Let's go.

12
00:00:38,958 --> 00:00:40,917
Meet back at the trucks. Be careful, okay?

13
00:00:42,750 --> 00:00:44,390
- Let's go. Quickly and quietly.
- Run fast.

14
00:00:44,417 --> 00:00:48,167
[man 2] Bring your things. Hurry. Come on.
Come on. Move it. Move it. Go, go, go.

15
00:00:49,208 --> 00:00:51,792
- Come on. Come on, quickly.
- Come on, Mia. Let's go.

16
00:00:55,250 --> 00:00:56,833
- [man 2] Hurry up. Quickly.
- Where?

17
00:00:56,917 --> 00:00:57,833
[man 3] This way.

18
00:00:57,917 --> 00:00:59,917
[whispered chatter]

19
00:01:04,750 --> 00:01:05,750
Move it. Move it.

20
00:01:07,167 --> 00:01:09,375
You two, follow me.
This way, guys. Come on!

21
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,000
This way.

22
00:01:15,875 --> 00:01:17,196
- Faster.
- [man 4 speaking Spanish]

23
00:01:18,417 --> 00:01:19,667
[man 2] Faster. Move it.

24
00:01:21,542 --> 00:01:23,917
- [woman breathing heavily]
- [man 2] Come on. Let's go.

25
00:01:26,583 --> 00:01:27,583
- You okay?
- [Mia] No.

26
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:29,167
Don't stop. Let's go.

27
00:01:29,667 --> 00:01:31,042
[snarling]

28
00:01:31,125 --> 00:01:32,500
[barking]

29
00:01:33,625 --> 00:01:35,625
That way.
Let's go. Come on. Move. You first.

30
00:01:35,708 --> 00:01:38,125
- Okay.
- [dogs continue barking]

31
00:01:38,208 --> 00:01:40,542
[Mia breathes quickly]

32
00:01:40,625 --> 00:01:42,625
[tense music plays]

33
00:01:44,625 --> 00:01:46,625
[helicopters rumble overhead]

34
00:01:48,042 --> 00:01:49,500
- [Mia] Nico.
- [Nico] I'm here.

35
00:01:51,708 --> 00:01:53,875
- I don't fit. Fuck, I don't fit!
- [Nico] You can do it.

36
00:01:53,958 --> 00:01:54,875
- Push me.
- [Nico] Okay.

37
00:01:54,958 --> 00:01:56,500
- [Mia struggles]
- [Nico] Sorry.

38
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:00,875
- Are you okay? Yeah, you're okay.
- [Mia] What?

39
00:02:00,958 --> 00:02:02,875
- [helicopter rumbles]
- [man 2] Back up!

40
00:02:06,875 --> 00:02:07,875
Let's go.

41
00:02:08,458 --> 00:02:09,458
Come on. Follow me.

42
00:02:11,875 --> 00:02:12,875
Hold my hand.

43
00:02:16,167 --> 00:02:17,167
Come on.

44
00:02:17,208 --> 00:02:18,333
[Nico] Let's go, love.

45
00:02:19,958 --> 00:02:21,458
[man 2] Stay back, don't move.

46
00:02:23,667 --> 00:02:24,667
Now!

47
00:02:27,625 --> 00:02:29,042
Through here. Almost there.

48
00:02:29,125 --> 00:02:31,476
[man 5 over megaphone]
<i>Attention! Put your hands in the air!</i>

49
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:33,083
<i>- Stay where you are.</i>
- [woman whimpers]

50
00:02:33,167 --> 00:02:36,458
<i>This is the police. You are under arrest.</i>

51
00:02:36,542 --> 00:02:37,542
Give me the money.

52
00:02:38,958 --> 00:02:39,958
You wait here.

53
00:02:40,417 --> 00:02:41,958
- Are you okay?
- [Mia] Okay.

54
00:02:42,875 --> 00:02:43,875
[exhales]

55
00:02:45,375 --> 00:02:47,215
Didn't tell me about these two.
Bring 'em over.

56
00:02:47,292 --> 00:02:48,292
You, here.

57
00:02:49,167 --> 00:02:50,167
It's fine.

58
00:02:51,958 --> 00:02:54,625
- Is anything wrong?
- The conditions are riskier than expected.

59
00:02:54,708 --> 00:02:55,792
I need more money.

60
00:02:55,875 --> 00:02:57,958
No, no, no. We don't have any more money.

61
00:03:01,708 --> 00:03:02,833
I see how this works.

62
00:03:04,667 --> 00:03:07,375
- Babe, give me your ring.
- [Mia] No.

63
00:03:07,458 --> 00:03:10,417
{\an8}-Yes. You've got to.
- No. We gave them everything. Not my ring!

64
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:12,458
Mia, we've got to leave now.

65
00:03:12,542 --> 00:03:13,542
Take it.

66
00:03:13,958 --> 00:03:14,958
Come on.

67
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,125
Come on. We don't have all night. Move it.

68
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:19,000
Good. This way.

69
00:03:19,458 --> 00:03:20,458
Safe travels.

70
00:03:24,417 --> 00:03:25,875
[Nico] We're gonna make it.

71
00:03:27,042 --> 00:03:29,083
There it is. Our luxury liner.

72
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:30,167
Move it, asshole!

73
00:03:31,083 --> 00:03:32,167
- Come on.
- [man 6] Let's go!

74
00:03:32,250 --> 00:03:33,125
[man 7] Now!

75
00:03:33,208 --> 00:03:35,208
[music swells]

76
00:03:42,792 --> 00:03:44,000
[man 8] Step to the back.

77
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:45,500
- Are you okay?
- No.

78
00:03:45,583 --> 00:03:47,250
[music crescendos and fades]

79
00:03:55,875 --> 00:03:57,083
[flashlight clicks]

80
00:03:58,958 --> 00:04:00,125
[woman 1] <i>There's no food!</i>

81
00:04:00,208 --> 00:04:02,250
[man 1] <i>We accepted</i>
<i>the discourse about shortages.</i>

82
00:04:02,333 --> 00:04:05,125
<i>We accepted that we had to make sacrifices
for the common good.</i>

83
00:04:05,208 --> 00:04:07,667
<i>We accepted
that measures would be temporary.</i>

84
00:04:08,167 --> 00:04:09,000
<i>But what now?</i>

85
00:04:09,083 --> 00:04:10,958
<i>Look how far they've pushed us.</i>

86
00:04:11,042 --> 00:04:14,083
<i>First, they exterminated the elderly
to deal with the shortages.</i>

87
00:04:14,167 --> 00:04:16,542
<i>Now they're targeting
pregnant women and kids.</i>

88
00:04:16,625 --> 00:04:19,583
<i>Don't you see it? Pregnant women and kids!</i>

89
00:04:19,667 --> 00:04:21,708
<i>The regime isn't ending shortages.</i>

90
00:04:21,792 --> 00:04:23,375
Is there anything else on?

91
00:04:23,458 --> 00:04:25,625
[man 1] <i>There are alternatives</i>
<i>to this massacre.</i>

92
00:04:25,708 --> 00:04:28,625
<i>Countries like Ireland,
Iceland, and Norway have managed to stop…</i>

93
00:04:28,708 --> 00:04:30,542
- [Nico] Yeah, take it off.
- [Mia] Okay.

94
00:04:30,625 --> 00:04:32,875
[man 1] <i>Our country</i>
<i>must follow their example and help…</i>

95
00:04:32,958 --> 00:04:34,375
[Mia sighs]

96
00:04:34,458 --> 00:04:35,708
[Nico] Let me see.

97
00:04:35,792 --> 00:04:37,458
Wow. [chuckles]

98
00:04:39,667 --> 00:04:40,667
That's better.

99
00:04:40,750 --> 00:04:42,083
- Okay? Here.
- Yeah.

100
00:04:42,167 --> 00:04:43,292
[baby cries]

101
00:04:51,083 --> 00:04:52,542
[woman 2] Make him shut up.

102
00:05:03,917 --> 00:05:04,917
[shushes]

103
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,125
[Mia] Where'd you get this?

104
00:05:06,208 --> 00:05:07,042
Ah…

105
00:05:07,125 --> 00:05:08,125
[Mia] Tell me.

106
00:05:08,750 --> 00:05:09,750
It's a secret.

107
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,583
Let's not have it now.

108
00:05:12,667 --> 00:05:14,875
Let's save it
and eat it when we get there.

109
00:05:14,958 --> 00:05:16,875
- To celebrate, right?
- Exactly.

110
00:05:18,167 --> 00:05:19,667
[Nico sighs]

111
00:05:22,083 --> 00:05:24,125
Do you think the regime will go there too?

112
00:05:25,250 --> 00:05:27,167
Ireland has ruled in opposition to it.

113
00:05:27,833 --> 00:05:30,250
Doesn't matter.
Governments are falling everywhere.

114
00:05:30,333 --> 00:05:32,583
- I'll tell you something about the Irish.
- What?

115
00:05:33,083 --> 00:05:34,958
It's impossible to overthrow them.

116
00:05:35,042 --> 00:05:37,333
- They drink dark beer.
- Right.

117
00:05:37,417 --> 00:05:38,875
Ireland won't give in.

118
00:05:40,750 --> 00:05:42,750
You're allowed to be afraid, you know.

119
00:05:43,792 --> 00:05:46,625
Everything will work out, you'll see. Hmm.

120
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:49,583
- You don't know for sure.
- The worst part is over.

121
00:05:49,667 --> 00:05:50,708
You don't know that.

122
00:05:52,375 --> 00:05:53,833
There's one thing I do know.

123
00:05:55,125 --> 00:05:56,125
[Mia] What?

124
00:05:56,667 --> 00:05:58,667
That I love you more than yesterday.

125
00:05:59,708 --> 00:06:00,958
But less than tomorrow.

126
00:06:10,708 --> 00:06:12,500
[drilling sounds]

127
00:06:19,833 --> 00:06:21,833
[truck engine revving]

128
00:06:23,667 --> 00:06:25,250
What's happening? Are we there?

129
00:06:25,875 --> 00:06:27,958
- [brakes hiss]
- [truck engine revving]

130
00:06:28,042 --> 00:06:29,042
We're leaving.

131
00:06:34,375 --> 00:06:36,750
- [phone beeps]
- [woman 2] Turn off the games.

132
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:48,333
[whispers] Do you think she's pregnant?
She's all alone.

133
00:06:53,792 --> 00:06:55,875
If she's pregnant, she's not alone.

134
00:07:03,958 --> 00:07:05,375
How's our little Noa doing?

135
00:07:06,875 --> 00:07:08,208
I didn't know we decided yet.

136
00:07:08,292 --> 00:07:10,375
- Noa.
- [sighs]

137
00:07:10,458 --> 00:07:13,083
- What do you wanna name her?
- I hope it isn't a girl.

138
00:07:13,792 --> 00:07:14,792
I mean it.

139
00:07:15,708 --> 00:07:18,167
Well, I think she's a girl, a warrior.

140
00:07:19,167 --> 00:07:20,417
Just like her mother.

141
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:21,500
I don't feel her.

142
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:23,750
What?

143
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:26,667
She hasn't kicked me in two days.

144
00:07:28,667 --> 00:07:30,208
[sighs] That's not good.

145
00:07:31,917 --> 00:07:33,083
Why didn't you tell me?

146
00:07:33,958 --> 00:07:34,958
Dunno.

147
00:07:40,417 --> 00:07:41,417
What are you doing?

148
00:07:42,208 --> 00:07:43,208
Haven't you noticed?

149
00:07:44,292 --> 00:07:46,250
She always pushes right here.

150
00:07:47,333 --> 00:07:48,625
I think this is a foot.

151
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,000
How do you do it?

152
00:07:52,708 --> 00:07:53,708
What?

153
00:07:57,125 --> 00:07:58,875
Act like everything's fine.

154
00:08:00,167 --> 00:08:01,875
Like nothing's happened to us.

155
00:08:02,375 --> 00:08:03,708
You know that's not true.

156
00:08:06,750 --> 00:08:08,208
- You know, don't you?
- Mm-hmm.

157
00:08:10,875 --> 00:08:12,875
[baby cries]

158
00:08:13,708 --> 00:08:14,542
[squeaking sound]

159
00:08:14,625 --> 00:08:16,208
[girl] You brought my duck!

160
00:08:16,292 --> 00:08:18,583
Hi, there. What's wrong?

161
00:08:18,667 --> 00:08:19,750
[women 3 shushes]

162
00:08:20,542 --> 00:08:22,333
Tsk, tsk, tsk, tsk.

163
00:08:22,417 --> 00:08:24,417
No, no, no. Don't cry.

164
00:08:25,375 --> 00:08:28,184
- [man 2] What does the duck say?
- [woman 3] Shh. Don't cry. You're okay.

165
00:08:28,208 --> 00:08:29,542
- Shh.
- Nico.

166
00:08:29,625 --> 00:08:30,625
[Nico] Yeah?

167
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:35,000
What if she's alive,

168
00:08:35,583 --> 00:08:37,125
and we're leaving her behind?

169
00:08:39,125 --> 00:08:40,125
All alone.

170
00:08:42,250 --> 00:08:43,250
She's not alive.

171
00:08:44,458 --> 00:08:45,458
They took her away,

172
00:08:46,583 --> 00:08:47,667
and they killed her.

173
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,000
[Mia] Hmm.

174
00:09:03,333 --> 00:09:05,792
- [truck rumbles]
- [brakes hiss]

175
00:09:05,875 --> 00:09:07,583
- [man whistles]
- [gasps]

176
00:09:07,667 --> 00:09:10,208
- [people arguing indistinctly]
- [thudding]

177
00:09:25,167 --> 00:09:26,542
- [clamoring]
- [Nico] Hey! Hey! Hey!

178
00:09:26,625 --> 00:09:27,625
[Mia] Nico! Nico!

179
00:09:28,958 --> 00:09:30,542
{\an8}-[grunts]
- Mia!

180
00:09:31,250 --> 00:09:32,708
Come on, now! Hurry up! Move it!

181
00:09:32,792 --> 00:09:34,208
Move it! Get in there now! Come on!

182
00:09:34,292 --> 00:09:36,792
What are you doin'?
Stop. There's too many. Back out!

183
00:09:36,875 --> 00:09:38,500
- Nico! Nico!
- Mia!

184
00:09:40,250 --> 00:09:43,583
- [gasps]
- Listen up! There's too many of you.

185
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:45,250
There's another truck coming.

186
00:09:45,333 --> 00:09:47,792
- Half of you get out. Now!
- You heard him! It's too full.

187
00:09:47,875 --> 00:09:50,667
- Get some of 'em out!
- [man 3] Come on! Come on! Get outta here!

188
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:53,625
Mia! Mia! Mia!

189
00:09:53,708 --> 00:09:55,208
- Nico!
- [man 4] Get out!

190
00:09:55,292 --> 00:09:57,012
- Wait! Mia!
- Come on, keep moving. Hey, you!

191
00:09:57,042 --> 00:09:58,750
- [grunts]
- You can't stay!

192
00:09:58,833 --> 00:10:01,417
Hey. Are you deaf or what?
Get off the truck.

193
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:04,042
No, no. I was on this one, with my wife!

194
00:10:04,125 --> 00:10:05,250
- Get out!
- Get out!

195
00:10:05,333 --> 00:10:06,792
[grunts]

196
00:10:06,875 --> 00:10:08,792
- [Mia] Nico!
- [man 4] The rest move back.

197
00:10:08,875 --> 00:10:11,667
- Stay back!
- No, no, no, no, no, no, no! Please! No!

198
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:20,000
[gasping in disbelief]

199
00:10:21,583 --> 00:10:24,583
No. No, no, no. Nico. No, no, no.

200
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:27,625
[gasping]

201
00:10:32,500 --> 00:10:34,625
Keep moving! Come on! To the back!

202
00:10:35,125 --> 00:10:37,333
[Mia] Nico. Nico. [sobs]

203
00:10:39,917 --> 00:10:41,208
Nico.

204
00:10:41,292 --> 00:10:42,417
Nico. No.

205
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,125
Nico, Nico.

206
00:10:44,208 --> 00:10:45,333
One-zero-seven green.

207
00:10:45,417 --> 00:10:47,833
- [truck engine revving]
- No. No, please. Wait, wait, wait.

208
00:10:50,917 --> 00:10:52,917
[line rings]

209
00:10:53,917 --> 00:10:55,625
- [Nico] <i>Mia</i>.
- Babe, are you all right?

210
00:10:55,708 --> 00:10:57,167
[pants] <i>Yeah, yeah, yeah, I'm fine.</i>

211
00:10:57,250 --> 00:10:58,875
- Okay, Nico.
<i>- Yeah?</i>

212
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:02,833
<i>- </i>How will we find each other again?
<i>- We're okay. My truck is behind yours.</i>

213
00:11:02,917 --> 00:11:04,333
- I can't do this alone.
<i>- What?</i>

214
00:11:04,417 --> 00:11:06,583
No, no.
I can't do it alone, I really can't.

215
00:11:06,667 --> 00:11:10,708
<i>Listen to me. You can't trust anyone.
Understand? Keep your things tucked away.</i>

216
00:11:10,792 --> 00:11:11,833
<i>Be careful, my love.</i>

217
00:11:12,333 --> 00:11:13,458
[Mia] Yeah. [sniffles]

218
00:11:14,083 --> 00:11:15,708
<i>- Did you hear me?</i>
- [helicopter whirring]

219
00:11:15,792 --> 00:11:17,750
<i>Mia, are you there? Mia!</i>

220
00:11:17,833 --> 00:11:19,250
Nico, listen to me.

221
00:11:19,333 --> 00:11:21,542
Are you sure they're taking us
to the same location?

222
00:11:21,625 --> 00:11:23,667
<i>Yes, and when they stop, I'll escape.</i>

223
00:11:23,750 --> 00:11:25,792
<i>Our ship is the only one
setting sail this week.</i>

224
00:11:25,875 --> 00:11:27,083
- Nico.
<i>- Yes?</i>

225
00:11:28,292 --> 00:11:29,708
I wanna be with you.

226
00:11:29,792 --> 00:11:31,000
<i>Me too. I love you, Mia.</i>

227
00:11:31,083 --> 00:11:33,083
<i>Don't worry,
everything's gonna be all right.</i>

228
00:11:33,167 --> 00:11:34,542
- Okay.
<i>- We're gonna be okay.</i>

229
00:11:35,042 --> 00:11:36,583
- Okay.
<i>- We'll talk soon, all right?</i>

230
00:11:36,667 --> 00:11:38,500
Don't go yet, don't hang up.

231
00:11:38,583 --> 00:11:40,958
<i>Love, we can't waste our batteries.</i>

232
00:11:41,042 --> 00:11:42,417
Please don't hang up yet.

233
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:44,583
<i>We'll be together again soon, you'll see.</i>

234
00:11:44,667 --> 00:11:45,792
- Nico.
<i>- Yeah?</i>

235
00:11:49,042 --> 00:11:49,917
Come soon.

236
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,958
<i>I will. As soon as I can.</i>

237
00:11:52,042 --> 00:11:53,083
Okay.

238
00:11:54,292 --> 00:11:56,292
[indistinct outside chatter]

239
00:11:58,167 --> 00:12:00,542
[man] What makes you think
you're better than us?

240
00:12:00,625 --> 00:12:02,625
[air raid siren blares]

241
00:12:03,917 --> 00:12:05,917
[cars honk]

242
00:12:07,708 --> 00:12:09,708
[all shouting indistinctly]

243
00:12:19,375 --> 00:12:20,375
[automatic gunfire]

244
00:12:22,750 --> 00:12:24,417
- [people screaming]
