00:59:08,167 --> 00:59:09,792
[Noa's cries fade]

781
00:59:10,750 --> 00:59:11,750
[exhales]

782
00:59:14,667 --> 00:59:16,125
[moaning softly]

783
00:59:25,667 --> 00:59:26,667
Mm.

784
00:59:30,583 --> 00:59:31,583
[groans softly]

785
00:59:38,667 --> 00:59:39,750
[retching]

786
00:59:46,958 --> 00:59:48,958
[haunting music plays]

787
01:00:11,167 --> 01:00:12,208
[moans softly]

788
01:00:14,042 --> 01:00:16,042
[Noa cries in the distance]

789
01:00:21,750 --> 01:00:24,208
- [Uma] Mommy?
- Uma, my darling.

790
01:00:25,792 --> 01:00:27,625
Uma, please come here.

791
01:00:28,500 --> 01:00:30,708
Come closer. Please. I wanna see you.

792
01:00:30,792 --> 01:00:32,667
[haunting music continues]

793
01:00:38,000 --> 01:00:39,000
Hi, honey.

794
01:00:40,167 --> 01:00:42,542
Mommy, can we go home now, please?

795
01:00:44,083 --> 01:00:46,292
I miss you so much, Uma.

796
01:00:46,375 --> 01:00:49,292
Mommy, why did you let them take me away?

797
01:00:50,542 --> 01:00:51,583
I'm sorry.

798
01:00:52,750 --> 01:00:53,833
[Uma sobs]

799
01:00:55,583 --> 01:00:56,583
I'm sorry.

800
01:00:57,792 --> 01:00:59,000
It was my fault.

801
01:01:00,417 --> 01:01:03,542
I just wanted to play with the airplane.

802
01:01:05,583 --> 01:01:07,792
I know, it was a mistake.

803
01:01:21,000 --> 01:01:22,042
[whispers] No, stay.

804
01:01:24,625 --> 01:01:25,625
I'm sorry.

805
01:01:28,000 --> 01:01:30,542
It was my fault. I messed up.

806
01:01:33,917 --> 01:01:35,000
I'm sorry.

807
01:01:39,417 --> 01:01:40,667
It wasn't your fault.

808
01:01:52,708 --> 01:01:53,833
It wasn't your fault.

809
01:02:00,250 --> 01:02:02,250
[water pattering]

810
01:02:05,833 --> 01:02:07,458
[Noa cries]

811
01:02:13,583 --> 01:02:15,583
[pleasant guitar music plays]

812
01:02:59,250 --> 01:03:01,292
[Mia] Mommy will
get you out of here, okay?

813
01:03:05,458 --> 01:03:07,458
[guitar music continues]

814
01:03:26,333 --> 01:03:28,333
[metal creaking]

815
01:03:32,542 --> 01:03:33,875
[groans]

816
01:03:39,333 --> 01:03:40,750
[straining]

817
01:03:47,708 --> 01:03:49,375
- [growls]
- [music swells]

818
01:04:06,208 --> 01:04:07,333
[laughs]

819
01:04:13,792 --> 01:04:15,667
[laughing]

820
01:04:20,708 --> 01:04:22,708
[cooing]

821
01:04:23,833 --> 01:04:25,833
[sweeping music playing]

822
01:05:09,708 --> 01:05:12,333
Sweetheart. Look at the world.

823
01:05:14,500 --> 01:05:16,250
Up above is the sky.

824
01:05:16,333 --> 01:05:18,167
Down below is the sea.

825
01:05:19,167 --> 01:05:22,042
And very far over there
is where we're going.

826
01:05:26,625 --> 01:05:28,542
Nico, where are you?

827
01:05:40,208 --> 01:05:41,750
Feels good to be outside, right?

828
01:05:42,250 --> 01:05:44,625
Yeah, you seem much happier.

829
01:05:44,708 --> 01:05:46,417
You like the sun and fresh air.

830
01:06:04,000 --> 01:06:05,208
[gasps]

831
01:06:07,792 --> 01:06:09,250
This way. Over here.

832
01:06:09,333 --> 01:06:10,333
Here.

833
01:06:11,000 --> 01:06:12,792
Come on. Over here. This way.

834
01:06:15,417 --> 01:06:17,000
[exciting music playing]

835
01:06:47,875 --> 01:06:48,875
[grunts]

836
01:06:55,333 --> 01:06:56,500
[groans weakly]

837
01:06:56,583 --> 01:06:58,583
[tense music playing]

838
01:07:05,417 --> 01:07:06,417
[groaning]

839
01:07:29,000 --> 01:07:31,000
[suspenseful music playing]

840
01:07:39,375 --> 01:07:40,375
[grunts]

841
01:07:48,250 --> 01:07:49,667
[screams]

842
01:07:51,208 --> 01:07:53,125
[groans in pain]

843
01:07:59,458 --> 01:08:00,667
Here. I'm here.

844
01:08:01,542 --> 01:08:02,542
[grunts]

845
01:08:04,125 --> 01:08:05,125
[groans impatiently]

846
01:08:07,833 --> 01:08:09,625
[groaning]

847
01:08:26,625 --> 01:08:27,667
[groaning]

848
01:08:34,458 --> 01:08:36,125
[Noa fussing]

849
01:08:37,542 --> 01:08:38,583
[groans in pain]

850
01:08:39,208 --> 01:08:40,208
[exhales]

851
01:08:42,625 --> 01:08:46,208
Shh! It's okay, my love.
I'm here. It's okay. It's okay.

852
01:08:46,292 --> 01:08:47,417
I'm here. I'm here.

853
01:08:52,958 --> 01:08:54,833
[screams]

854
01:08:54,917 --> 01:08:56,708
- [groaning]
- [Noa crying]

855
01:08:59,375 --> 01:09:00,500
[groaning weakly]

856
01:09:07,250 --> 01:09:08,083
[groans]

857
01:09:08,167 --> 01:09:09,917
Oh my God. Oh my God. Oh my God.

858
01:09:10,000 --> 01:09:11,042
[inhales]

859
01:09:11,542 --> 01:09:12,583
[exhales] I've got this.

860
01:09:14,250 --> 01:09:15,667
[groans]

861
01:09:17,708 --> 01:09:19,708
[Noa coos in the distance]

862
01:09:23,833 --> 01:09:24,833
[groans]

863
01:09:32,417 --> 01:09:33,625
[coos]

864
01:09:33,708 --> 01:09:35,542
- [Noa cries]
- Oh.

865
01:09:37,417 --> 01:09:38,542
Don't worry, sweetie.

866
01:09:38,625 --> 01:09:40,042
[groans]

867
01:09:45,208 --> 01:09:46,750
[shuddering]

868
01:10:09,375 --> 01:10:11,375
[Mia humming melody]

869
01:10:40,167 --> 01:10:42,167
[hopeful music plays]

870
01:11:11,458 --> 01:11:12,458
Come on.

871
01:11:13,000 --> 01:11:15,542
Come on, come on.

872
01:11:18,167 --> 01:11:19,167
Come on.

873
01:11:20,417 --> 01:11:22,958
Come on, come on. Come, come, come, come.

874
01:11:26,000 --> 01:11:27,000
Come on.

875
01:11:30,000 --> 01:11:31,292
Come on.

876
01:11:32,583 --> 01:11:33,708
[gasps]

877
01:11:36,083 --> 01:11:37,125
[gasps]

878
01:11:37,208 --> 01:11:39,208
[gentle music playing]

879
01:11:52,250 --> 01:11:55,125
Don't give me that look. I'm desperate.
You know what it feels like.

880
01:12:07,167 --> 01:12:08,458
MAXIMUM

881
01:12:08,542 --> 01:12:13,042
DAY 9

882
01:12:13,125 --> 01:12:15,125
[stirring guitar music playing]

883
01:12:28,917 --> 01:12:30,417
[Noa cries]

884
01:12:48,625 --> 01:12:50,875
[Mia] Good job. You're Mommy's big girl.

885
01:12:54,083 --> 01:12:55,250
It's mini bath time.

886
01:12:56,917 --> 01:12:58,917
[dramatic music playing]

887
01:13:17,542 --> 01:13:20,542
Where are you? Where are you?
Call me. Come on, Nico. Call me.

888
01:13:20,625 --> 01:13:22,583
Call me, please. Call me!

889
01:13:46,833 --> 01:13:50,583
DAY 12

890
01:14:06,750 --> 01:14:07,750
[music fades]

891
01:14:09,542 --> 01:14:10,792
[Mia] Look, this is me.

892
01:14:10,875 --> 01:14:11,875
At school.

893
01:14:13,167 --> 01:14:15,792
With one of my students.
Did I tell you I'm a teacher?

894
01:14:17,000 --> 01:14:19,500
This is your daddy. His name's Nico.

895
01:14:19,583 --> 01:14:21,417
He's at work, in our store.

896
01:14:22,750 --> 01:14:26,375
We were forced to close the store
because there wasn't much food to sell.

897
01:14:26,875 --> 01:14:31,625
At the end, there wasn't anything at all.
But people came to visit him anyway.

898
01:14:32,208 --> 01:14:33,667
Because he cared about them.

899
01:14:33,750 --> 01:14:36,542
I know he'll find a way
to get us out of here

900
01:14:36,625 --> 01:14:39,958
because… he always knows what to do.

901
01:14:43,833 --> 01:14:44,750
[sniffs]

902
01:14:44,833 --> 01:14:47,083
This is your grandma, Noa.

903
01:14:48,042 --> 01:14:50,083
Do you like that name? Noa.

904
01:14:50,875 --> 01:14:52,083
I think it's beautiful.

905
01:14:52,167 --> 01:14:54,708
It means "long life." Spelled with an H.

906
01:14:55,750 --> 01:14:57,292
But it's prettier without it.

907
01:14:57,375 --> 01:14:59,583
In Noah's Ark, that's a story,

908
01:15:00,500 --> 01:15:02,292
they survived and got to land.

909
01:15:04,500 --> 01:15:07,167
There are animals in it.
I'll read it to you some day.

910
01:15:11,833 --> 01:15:12,875
This is Uma.

911
01:15:14,042 --> 01:15:15,917
You wanna know about her, don't you?

912
01:15:16,000 --> 01:15:18,000
[gentle music plays]

913
01:15:20,417 --> 01:15:23,500
Well, you know,
you have the same eyes as she did.

914
01:15:23,583 --> 01:15:24,583
Exactly.

915
01:15:24,958 --> 01:15:27,958
And when she was a baby,
the shape of her face was just like yours.

916
01:15:28,042 --> 01:15:30,417
She wanted to be an airplane pilot.

917
01:15:30,917 --> 01:15:33,125
She liked to say "airplane pilot."

918
01:15:33,708 --> 01:15:35,375
You would've had fun with her.

919
01:15:38,750 --> 01:15:40,375
What happened is that when…

920
01:15:43,583 --> 01:15:45,250
[shudders] …when the regime took over,

921
01:15:45,333 --> 01:15:47,875
we were forced to lock ourselves
inside the house.

922
01:15:47,958 --> 01:15:50,417
And your daddy would go out
to get us food.

923
01:15:51,250 --> 01:15:53,792
At first, it was fine,
but as time went on…

924
01:15:56,917 --> 01:15:59,458
Uma wanted to go outside because…

925
01:16:01,708 --> 01:16:04,417
because a girl can't stand
being locked up for too long

926
01:16:05,583 --> 01:16:07,250
in her house, you know.

927
01:16:12,750 --> 01:16:14,625
There wasn't enough room to play,

928
01:16:16,000 --> 01:16:17,375
so one day,

929
01:16:19,042 --> 01:16:21,917
she kept begging me
and insisting we go out.

930
01:16:24,083 --> 01:16:25,333
And, um,

931
01:16:25,917 --> 01:16:27,250
I said, "Okay."

932
01:16:28,583 --> 01:16:31,292
We were only outside five minutes,
but they took her.

933
01:16:41,000 --> 01:16:42,000
It was all my fault.

934
01:16:42,792 --> 01:16:44,042
I should've known better.

935
01:16:46,333 --> 01:16:47,417
I messed up.

936
01:16:51,750 --> 01:16:52,792
[sighs]

937
01:16:54,875 --> 01:16:56,875
[exhales]

938
01:17:05,708 --> 01:17:06,708
[Noa coughs]

939
01:17:08,000 --> 01:17:09,750
- [Noa cries]
- [Mia] What's wrong?

940
01:17:10,542 --> 01:17:12,583
- [coughs]
- What's wrong? Are you okay?

941
01:17:12,667 --> 01:17:14,125
- You're freezing.
- [wailing]

942
01:17:26,500 --> 01:17:27,500
There we are.

943
01:17:34,000 --> 01:17:36,292
You're snug as a bug in a rug like that.

944
01:17:37,292 --> 01:17:38,750
My beanie looks cute on you.

945
01:17:39,958 --> 01:17:40,958
[chuckles softly]

946
01:17:41,583 --> 01:17:43,625
You'll feel much better tomorrow, okay?

947
01:17:44,792 --> 01:17:46,000
You're all bundled up.

948
01:17:47,417 --> 01:17:48,542
Warm and cozy.

949
01:17:50,167 --> 01:17:52,500
[hums melody]

950
01:17:54,250 --> 01:17:57,625
<i>♪ Has anybody said to you ♪</i>

951
01:17:59,458 --> 01:18:02,625
<i>♪ Dreams that you dream ♪</i>

952
01:18:04,833 --> 01:18:08,500
<i>♪ Live outside of space or time ♪</i>

953
01:18:09,667 --> 01:18:14,750
<i>♪ And only in your mind? ♪</i>

954
01:18:16,167 --> 01:18:18,667
<i>♪ La la ♪</i>

955
01:18:20,958 --> 01:18:23,583
<i>♪ La la ♪</i>

956
01:18:25,542 --> 01:18:28,083
[choir sings] <i>♪ La la ♪</i>

957
01:18:30,250 --> 01:18:32,417
<i>♪ La la ♪</i>

958
01:18:34,708 --> 01:18:41,375
<i>♪ La la, la la, la la ♪</i>

959
01:18:44,917 --> 01:18:47,167
["NANA (Cap.9: Concepción)"
by ROSALÍA plays]

960
01:19:44,625 --> 01:19:45,625
[thud on wood]

961
01:19:45,708 --> 01:19:46,750
[song fades]

962
01:19:52,083 --> 01:19:53,917
[thudding continues]

963
01:20:03,542 --> 01:20:07,000
[shushes] Sweet pea. All right. I got you.

964
01:20:11,000 --> 01:20:12,083
[thudding continues]

965
01:20:14,500 --> 01:20:15,625
DAY 12

966
01:20:17,500 --> 01:20:19,167
- [Mia] No, no, no.
- [thudding continues]

967
01:20:19,250 --> 01:20:21,042
MAXIMUM

968
01:20:22,208 --> 01:20:23,208
[thudding continues]

969
01:20:29,583 --> 01:20:30,792
[thudding continues]

970
01:20:35,000 --> 01:20:36,417
[shushes, groans]

971
01:20:58,542 --> 01:21:00,542
[phone rings]

972
01:21:05,000 --> 01:21:06,667
Nico! Nico!

973
01:21:06,750 --> 01:21:08,833
Oh, come on, come on, connect.
Please, come on.

974
01:21:08,917 --> 01:21:11,708
Please work. Come on, connect. Connect.

975
01:21:11,792 --> 01:21:12,792
[yelps]

976
01:21:13,208 --> 01:21:14,833
Nico. Nico.

977
01:21:14,917 --> 01:21:16,875
- [Nico] <i>Mia.</i>
- Can you hear me?

978
01:21:16,958 --> 01:21:19,542
- [laughs] <i>Uh, yes, at last.</i>
- It's finally you, my love.

979
01:21:19,625 --> 01:21:21,000
I'm so sorry I couldn't call you.

980
01:21:21,083 --> 01:21:23,333
I didn't have a signal.
And my cell is broken.

981
01:21:23,417 --> 01:21:25,917
No, no, I mean the screen is broken.
Where are you?

982
01:21:26,000 --> 01:21:28,292
<i>- Listen to me, please, my love.</i>
<i>- </i>What's wrong, Nico?

983
01:21:28,375 --> 01:21:29,417
[Nico sighs]

984
01:21:29,500 --> 01:21:31,167
<i>I won't be able to come for you.</i>

985
01:21:31,667 --> 01:21:33,375
<i>You'll have to make it on your own.</i>

986
01:21:34,625 --> 01:21:35,625
<i>Promise me you will.</i>

987
01:21:37,250 --> 01:21:38,250
<i>Promise.</i>

988
01:21:38,750 --> 01:21:40,458
- Nico, what's wrong?
- [Nico sniffs]

989
01:21:41,042 --> 01:21:43,625
- Please, Nico. I'm scared. What's wrong?
- [Nico coughing]

990
01:21:43,708 --> 01:21:44,750
My love, tell me.

991
01:21:45,375 --> 01:21:46,917
[Nico gulps air]

992
01:21:47,000 --> 01:21:48,708
[Nico panting]

993
01:21:48,792 --> 01:21:51,583
- Nico…
<i>- I'm… I'm hiding in a container.</i>

994
01:21:52,458 --> 01:21:56,542
<i>I snuck onto a ship, but they found me.</i>

995
01:21:57,208 --> 01:21:59,125
<i>And when I ran, they shot me.</i>

996
01:22:01,125 --> 01:22:02,375
Are you hurt?

997
01:22:03,625 --> 01:22:05,083
<i>I'm losing so much blood.</i>

998
01:22:06,000 --> 01:22:07,500
- What?
<i>- My love…</i>

999
01:22:08,333 --> 01:22:09,167
[Nico sniffles]

1000
01:22:09,250 --> 01:22:12,458
<i>- </i>Honey?
<i>- I just… I just wanted to say goodbye.</i>

1001
01:22:13,375 --> 01:22:14,375
[Nico sobs]

1002
01:22:14,875 --> 01:22:17,125
<i>And I want you to know that I fought hard.</i>

1003
01:22:18,042 --> 01:22:20,458
<i>I fought hard. As hard as I could.</i>

1004
01:22:21,833 --> 01:22:23,042
<i>I promise I did.</i>

1005
01:22:23,125 --> 01:22:25,750
[sniffles] <i>And… you were right.</i>

1006
01:22:26,250 --> 01:22:27,625
<i>You were always right.</i>

1007
01:22:28,458 --> 01:22:29,708
<i>I'm too optimistic.</i>

1008
01:22:30,542 --> 01:22:31,917
<i>We should've stayed.</i>

1009
01:22:32,000 --> 01:22:33,000
[Nico sobbing]

1010
01:22:33,083 --> 01:22:35,833
- No. No. Nico, listen to me.
- <i>I'm sorry.</i>

1011
01:22:35,917 --> 01:22:37,167
- Listen to me, Nico.
<i>- So sorry.</i>

1012
01:22:37,250 --> 01:22:38,542
Please, my love, listen to me.

1013
01:22:38,625 --> 01:22:40,750
- You saved our lives.
- <i>How?</i>

1014
01:22:40,833 --> 01:22:44,042
- Understand?
<i>- How? You said "our lives"?</i>

1015
01:22:44,125 --> 01:22:45,833
Yes, my love, she's here.

1016
01:22:45,917 --> 01:22:46,917
[Nico gasps]

1017
01:22:48,417 --> 01:22:50,750
She's here, Nico. She was born.

1018
01:22:50,833 --> 01:22:52,792
- [chuckling]
- [Nico chuckling, sobbing]

1019
01:22:52,875 --> 01:22:54,583
She's a beautiful little girl.

1020
01:22:54,667 --> 01:22:56,125
<i>- That's amazing.</i>
- Yeah.

1021
01:22:56,208 --> 01:22:58,375
<i>A girl, huh? See, I knew it.</i>

1022
01:22:59,542 --> 01:23:00,625
<i>Are you okay?</i>

1023
01:23:00,708 --> 01:23:03,875
- Yeah. We're both fine. We're both fine.
<i>- I wish I were with you.</i>

1024
01:23:03,958 --> 01:23:07,208
You're here, Nico.
You are. You've been here the whole time.

1025
01:23:07,292 --> 01:23:09,583
You were here during my labor,

1026
01:23:09,667 --> 01:23:12,375
you were here
when I finally opened the container.

1027
01:23:14,292 --> 01:23:16,250
I promised I wouldn't give up
and I fought.

1028
01:23:16,333 --> 01:23:20,458
I fought so hard.
And you're here when I sing to her.

1029
01:23:20,542 --> 01:23:21,875
You're always here with me.

1030
01:23:21,958 --> 01:23:25,458
<i>- What? You, sing?</i>
- Yes.

1031
01:23:25,542 --> 01:23:26,542
[Nico laughs]

1032
01:23:27,333 --> 01:23:30,458
[sniffles] <i>Sweetheart,</i>
<i>what does she look like?</i>

1033
01:23:32,708 --> 01:23:33,708
She looks like you.

1034
01:23:33,792 --> 01:23:36,875
She's so beautiful,
she's strong, and funny.

1035
01:23:36,958 --> 01:23:39,833
She makes me laugh,
